---
import { AMORTIZATION } from '../../data/tiers';
import HonestyNote from '../ui/HonestyNote.astro';
---

<div class="gb-grid gb-grid--2" data-rise>
	<article class="gb-card">
		<h3>The multi-tenant math</h3>
		<p>
			The dedicated-stack prices above are the <em>worst case</em> — one tenant carrying a whole stack.
			In a shared deployment the planes and engine clusters are shared, so a new tenant adds only a
			schema plus a few MiB of RAM. One Pro host (~${AMORTIZATION.proHostUsd}/mo) across
			~{AMORTIZATION.tenantsPerHost} tenants ≈ <strong>{AMORTIZATION.perTenant}</strong>.
		</p>
	</article>
	<HonestyNote title="Yes, that means the upper tiers have fat margins.">
		{AMORTIZATION.marginal} The markup funds support, SLAs and development — we'd rather show you that
		math than pretend it doesn't exist.
	</HonestyNote>
</div>
